cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.CC, cs.DC, cs.DS

The paper deals with a secure communication protocol and its implementation, which falls under the category of cryptography (cs.CR). It also involves information theory (cs.IT) in terms of achieving maximum throughput. The paper proposes a computationally secure protocol, which involves computational complexity (cs.CC). The protocol also involves distributed computing (cs.DC) as it involves multiple participants. Finally, the paper deals with detecting disruptors, which falls under the category of distributed systems (cs.DS).
